<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Defs>
    <!--
        RELIGION CATEGORY STYLE SORTING DEFS
        =====================================
        
        These defs allow you to categorize style categories as Religion, Ideology, or Both.
        This controls whether a style appears only in religion, only in ideology, or both.
        
        Category values:
            - "Religion"  = style only appears in religion system
            - "Ideology"  = style only appears in ideology system
            - "Both"      = style appears in both systems
        
        Default (no entry): "Both" — all styles appear in both systems by default.
        You only need to add entries if you want to RESTRICT a style to one system.
        
        
        HOW TO MAKE A PATCH (for mod authors)
        ======================================
        
        If your mod adds custom style categories and you want to restrict them to one system,
        create an XML file in your mod's Defs/ directory with entries like this:
        
        <Defs>
            <IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryStyleDef>
                <defName>CatStyle_YourStyleName</defName>
                <targetDefName>YourStyleCategoryDefName</targetDefName>
                <category>Religion</category>
            </IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryStyleDef>
        </Defs>
        
        The defName must be unique across all mods.
        The targetDefName must match your StyleCategoryDef's defName exactly.
        
        Examples:
            "Religion" = sacred art, religious architecture, spiritual symbols
            "Ideology" = political art, modern architecture, secular symbols
            "Both"     = general aesthetic styles that work in both contexts
        
        To modify an existing entry, use XML patching:
        
        <Defs>
            <IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryStyleDef Name="CatStyle_ExistingDef">
                <category>Both</category>
            </IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryStyleDef>
        </Defs>
    -->
</Defs>
